-- Nissan says to cut 20,000 workers worldwide
-- 
-- Mon Feb 9, 2009 2:36am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/02/09/us-nissan-jobs-sb-idUSTRE5181ZN20090209

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Nissan Motor Co said on Monday it would lay off 20,000 workers worldwide in the year from April 1. 

 The automaker also said it was cutting capital spending by 21 percent in the year to March 31 and would cut such outlays by a further 14 percent in the year from April. (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim )